    "created_at": "2015-12-03T01:35:47Z",
    "updated_at": "2015-12-03T01:35:47Z",
    "body": "The Windows system allocator has no way to specify alignment so the Rust code that invokes it is responsible for over-allocating and aligning. Therefore any concerns about whether it handles silly huge alignments can easily be resolved by just fixing the Rust code if any problems turn up.\n",
    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
